<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xmi:XMI xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1">
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-O_4ucp0Z5IAvaO4urZ-AVA" name="Plan functional safety assessment activities,_IzoH8JdtEeCPtY0LnWkRDw" guid="-O_4ucp0Z5IAvaO4urZ-AVA">
    <refinedDescription>The functional safety assessment plan is based upon the ASIL levels of the item under development and the contents of ISO&#xD;
26262 vol 2, clause 6.4.6 table 1 and 2 (&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
href=&quot;./../../practice.compliance.iso26262.base-ibm/tasks/Determine%20confirmation%20measures_101A6AFA.html&quot;&#xD;
guid=&quot;_04W6sIh2EeCE4bK4CwiExg&quot;>Determine confirmation measures&lt;/a>) . Which outlines the tasks and independence of safety&#xD;
auditors for a particular ASIL level and scope and depth of the assessment.</refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-1brGvqzOJUVxmxXA1M1WLw" name="Plan system level safety activities,_IzoH8ZdtEeCPtY0LnWkRDw" guid="-1brGvqzOJUVxmxXA1M1WLw">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The activities during the development of the lifecycle are phased around the item under development. The task of&#xD;
    systems engineering is carried out iteratively at different levels of development, the tasks being repeated at the&#xD;
    subsystems level.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The diagram below gives an&amp;nbsp;example of the flows and activities that need to be carried out for an item consisting&#xD;
    of number of subsystems consisting of combinations of hardware and software elements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;resources/PD3%20at%20systems%20level.png&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;600&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-3ZOtgezS50KddeuPzxhC2Q" name="Plan validation activities,_IzoH8pdtEeCPtY0LnWkRDw" guid="-3ZOtgezS50KddeuPzxhC2Q">
    <refinedDescription>Develop plan of the activities required to provide evidence that the item complies to the safety goals, that they are&#xD;
correct, complete and achieved at the vehicle level. This plan should also validate that the safety concepts are&#xD;
appropriate for the functional safety of the item.</refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-IGWXHpL-gzxSLoDxVfcnmA" name="Safety Manager,_V6Uu8ZkOEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-IGWXHpL-gzxSLoDxVfcnmA">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-pTb2Q-V48VHqn1DYdBQMjA" name="Project_Manager,_V6Uu9JkOEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-pTb2Q-V48VHqn1DYdBQMjA">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;div style=&quot;MARGIN-LEFT: 2em&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
        Assigns the safety manager&lt;br />&#xD;
        Ensures that the safety activities are performed and compliance with ISO26262 is achieved&lt;br />&#xD;
        Verifies that the organisation has provided the required resources to carry out the functional safety activities&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/div></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-lzpmAyBrQq5WQDysW1rqnA" name="Preliminary architectural assumptions,_V6UvAJkOEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-lzpmAyBrQq5WQDysW1rqnA">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Defines the initial architecture constraints and assumptions, it could be a textual and diagrammatic&#xD;
    of&amp;nbsp;description of the architecture or a SysML model that also captures the functional concept, operating modes and&#xD;
    systems states.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-sCCJTDfA4l2tkS3QfeuPOA" name="Item Definition,_V6UvA5kOEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-sCCJTDfA4l2tkS3QfeuPOA">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The item definition covers a number areas, it cover initial sets of requirements, functional (behavioural),&#xD;
    non-functional (environmental, performance or quality of service) or legal (laws, national and international&#xD;
    standards). It also consists of the definition of he behaviour and how flaws in that behaviour might result in&#xD;
    potential hazards or be derived from potential faults.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Finally it looks at how the item interacts with its surrounding systems and captures the interfaces,&#xD;
    interactions&amp;nbsp;and requirements that influence the item.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-vm-m6z-vFAZ8vkOScJbgQA" name="Item integration and testing plan,_V6UvBpkOEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-vm-m6z-vFAZ8vkOScJbgQA">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The integration and test plan is scoped to the system and vehicle level and considers information such as the&#xD;
    specification of the integration test (so that issues arising from the HW and SW verifications are included), the&#xD;
    interfaces between subsystems and the environment and all the relevant configuration and calibration data for all&#xD;
    variants of the item that are intended for production.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The user is referred to ISO 26262 Vol 4, clause 7.4.11 for further details.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-XsLqlwLq0OLdmYgXe8BOVQ" name="Carry out confirmation review of the item integration and test plan,_xHKOkKlzEeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-XsLqlwLq0OLdmYgXe8BOVQ">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Review to confirm that the item integration and test plan has been developed according to the requirements detailed in&#xD;
    ISO 26262, vol 4, Clause 5.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Independence of the reviewer is dependent upon the ASIL level of the items being integrated see &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.compliance.iso26262.base-ibm/tasks/Determine%20confirmation%20measures_101A6AFA.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_04W6sIh2EeCE4bK4CwiExg&quot;>Determine confirmation measures&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-ZyZRDquUT5gxQ_E8AN-5xw" name="Carry out confirmation review of the validation plan,_LI3yEKl2EeCC2aJoFcjzgA" guid="-ZyZRDquUT5gxQ_E8AN-5xw">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Review to confirm that the&amp;nbsp;validation plan has been developed according to the requirements detailed in ISO 26262,&#xD;
    vol 4, Clause 5.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Independence of the reviewer is dependent upon the ASIL level of the items being integrated see &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.compliance.iso26262.base-ibm/tasks/Determine%20confirmation%20measures_101A6AFA.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_04W6sIh2EeCE4bK4CwiExg&quot;>Determine confirmation measures&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-kDWKC5wo9_RPV6DXs3IeFg" name="Develop technical safety requirements,_V8YnoJkSEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-kDWKC5wo9_RPV6DXs3IeFg">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The technical safety requirements describe how to implement the functional safety concept at the Item/system level and&#xD;
    later on how this implementation is allocated down to HW and SW elements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The development of the technical safety requirements can be achieved with a combination of requirements management and&#xD;
    modeling techniques based upon SysML or UML. This is especially useful when defining interfaces, transitions between&#xD;
    operating modes and safer modes, constraints (non functional, environmental, timing etc).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    See &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/Architectural%20Design%20-%20uc_E8CAF5DD.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_H1zdAa3hEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>Architectural Design - Use-Case based&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is advised that the user refers to the&amp;nbsp;detailed requirements around this task in ISO 26262, vol 4, Clause&#xD;
    6.4.1-6.4.10&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-iJclzPJWZvDT7HyCIVc7ig" name="Refine Validation Plan,_V8YnoZkSEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-iJclzPJWZvDT7HyCIVc7ig">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Specification&amp;nbsp;of the validation criteria concerning&amp;nbsp;functional safety.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Defines how the item is validated against the customer requirements. It captures the configuration and calibration and&#xD;
    data of the item to be validated, along with test procedures, test cases and acceptance criteria. Information regarding&#xD;
    the equipment to be test and environmental conditions are also required to define the validation plan.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-MvwIPQpu-gL3UFhC2FdQEg" name="Verify technical safety requirements,_V8YnopkSEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-MvwIPQpu-gL3UFhC2FdQEg">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;Analysis of the technical safety requirements to ensure compliance with the functional safety concept and the&#xD;
    preliminary architectural design.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The verification is based upon the supporting processes detailed in ISO 26262, vol 8, clause 9, (&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../process.compliance.iso26262.base-ibm/capabilitypatterns/8.9%20Verification%20Planning_831C2385.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_91quQZEZEeCUs8vNyweFYw&quot;>8.9 Verification Planning&lt;/a>).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-XZUpQdP_F7oB_FiUXCie6w" name="Preliminary architectural assumptions,_V8YnrZkSEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-XZUpQdP_F7oB_FiUXCie6w">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Defines the initial architecture constraints and assumptions, it could be a textual and diagrammatic&#xD;
    of&amp;nbsp;description of the architecture or a SysML model that also captures the functional concept, operating modes and&#xD;
    systems states.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-FBEFI4BlNRWiPYtefDEi3w" name="Functional concept,_V8YnsZkSEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-FBEFI4BlNRWiPYtefDEi3w">
    <refinedDescription>Gives the users a conceptual highlevel understanding of the functionality of the system. This could be captured as textual&#xD;
document but it could also be&amp;nbsp;represented as a&amp;nbsp;SysML&amp;nbsp;functional model for the item under development. The&#xD;
SysML model may also capture the various operating modes and states and architectural assumptions at the vehicle level.</refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-u7mpewH2HbEkG-2IOhj5Nw" name="Safety goals,_V8Yns5kSEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-u7mpewH2HbEkG-2IOhj5Nw">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The safety goals are the top level safety requirements for the item. They provide the basis for the functional safety&#xD;
    requirements needed to avoid an unreasonable risk for each hazard. As safety goals are a form of requirement they&#xD;
    should not be expressed in terms of a solution but in terms of functional objectives.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-yvK6SWXGhLvoIWwe0yYfSA" name="Requirements Engineer,_5ql4p5wUEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-yvK6SWXGhLvoIWwe0yYfSA">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Identifies, analyses and structures requirements so that they are captured in an understandable and logical manner.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Aids with creating traceability links and baselines for requirements management.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription xmi:id="-1lOQx8cXDTP5aCji42gYSA" name="Develop technical safety architecture,_2mntEZzfEeCBU9GxbrSLZw" guid="-1lOQx8cXDTP5aCji42gYSA">
    <usageGuidance>If using model based techniques then it is advised that the following guidance is employed, use either &lt;a&#xD;
class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/Architectural%20Design%20-%20uc_E8CAF5DD.html&quot;&#xD;
guid=&quot;_H1zdAa3hEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>Architectural Design - Use-Case based&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;or &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/Architectural%20Design%20-%20op_54664526.html&quot;&#xD;
guid=&quot;_E9oWAa3hEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>Architectural Design - Operation based&lt;/a>. These methods also provide the basis for&#xD;
deriving the HW-SW interface specification and the systems design specification.</usageGuidance>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-mFMX5s3VDyz0j4Fmyq5R2w" name="Allocate safety requirements to HW and SW,_Z3hSEJzkEeCk2aQcgmZB_w" guid="-mFMX5s3VDyz0j4Fmyq5R2w">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This task is to some extent carried out in parallel with the development of the technical safety concept as assumptions&#xD;
    have to be made based upon ASIL decomposition and the systematic fault analysis as to the means by which a safety&#xD;
    requirement is implemented in HW or SW.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Their&amp;nbsp;must be a 100 % coverage of safety requirements to either HW and or SW elements, either directly or by&#xD;
    refinement.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-gLKtxpmM1RgE3gZdyWmvjQ" name="Requirements Engineer,_Z3hSE5zkEeCk2aQcgmZB_w" guid="-gLKtxpmM1RgE3gZdyWmvjQ">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Identifies, analyses and structures requirements so that they are captured in an understandable and logical manner.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Aids with creating traceability links and baselines for requirements management.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-JJI1fXlN5uo29UAH7WWK6Q" name="Develop system design,_bG85oJzkEeCk2aQcgmZB_w" guid="-JJI1fXlN5uo29UAH7WWK6Q">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Although the system design is not brought out as a work product in ISO 26262, it is essential to capture it for the&#xD;
    purpose of the refined system verification report that ensures that the proposed system design realises the intent of&#xD;
    the technical safety concepts.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The nature of the system design can be model based, this an appropriate medium for a number methods that can be used to&#xD;
    verify the system design which are recommended or highly recommended for according to the applied ASIL level, these&#xD;
    include System design inspection, system design walkthroughs, simulation and safety analyses.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If a model based approach is developed further, with the appropriate tools it is possible that system prototyping and&#xD;
    vehicle tests can also be carried out.&#xD;
&lt;/p>If using model based techniques then it is advised that the following guidance is employed, use either &lt;a&#xD;
class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/Architectural%20Design%20-%20uc_E8CAF5DD.html&quot;&#xD;
guid=&quot;_H1zdAa3hEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>Architectural Design - Use-Case based&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;or &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/Architectural%20Design%20-%20op_54664526.html&quot;&#xD;
guid=&quot;_E9oWAa3hEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>Architectural Design - Operation based&lt;/a>. These methods also provide the basis for&#xD;
deriving the HW-SW interface specification and the systems design specification.&lt;br /></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-jgx7TeI8axIq6QcyCqLLkQ" name="Develop technical safety concept,_bywPsJzkEeCk2aQcgmZB_w" guid="-jgx7TeI8axIq6QcyCqLLkQ">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This task is used to define the architecture of the item according to the ASIL designation of the requirements that&#xD;
    have been allocated to it and its respective subsystems.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The primary inputs to this phase are the functional concept, the technical safety requirements and the preliminary&#xD;
    architectural assumptions. The consistency across these products with the technical safety concept shall be ensured.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The verifiability of the system design, the effectiveness of the HW and SW development and the systems testability&#xD;
    through system integration should all be considered during the systems design and development.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is recommended that developers examine ISO 26262 Vol 4, clause 7.4.1 through 7.4.4&amp;nbsp;and 7.4.6 in detail to fully&#xD;
    appreciate the&amp;nbsp;guidance on developing the technical safety concept.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The steps indicated in this section are summaries of&amp;nbsp;considerations that need to be made and again it is advised&#xD;
    that developers follow the guidelines indicated.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-3n9ZYB5V0dZwXRcXPStfmA" name="Preliminary architectural assumptions,_bywPuZzkEeCk2aQcgmZB_w" guid="-3n9ZYB5V0dZwXRcXPStfmA">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Defines the initial architecture constraints and assumptions, it could be a textual and diagrammatic&#xD;
    of&amp;nbsp;description of the architecture or a SysML model that also captures the functional concept, operating modes and&#xD;
    systems states.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-1xnnHDloqngIXx4Xie2JWA" name="Functional concept,_bywPu5zkEeCk2aQcgmZB_w" guid="-1xnnHDloqngIXx4Xie2JWA">
    <refinedDescription>Gives the users a conceptual highlevel understanding of the functionality of the system. This could be captured as textual&#xD;
document but it could also be&amp;nbsp;represented as a&amp;nbsp;SysML&amp;nbsp;functional model for the item under development. The&#xD;
SysML model may also capture the various operating modes and states and architectural assumptions at the vehicle level.</refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-gweHFqf85p-Pky2q0s2paA" name="Refine System design to HW and SW level,_dJojEJzkEeCk2aQcgmZB_w" guid="-gweHFqf85p-Pky2q0s2paA">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This tasks is a continuance of the development of the system design down to the HW and SW level.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The nature of the system design can be model based, this an appropriate medium for a number methods that can be used to&#xD;
    verify the system design which are recommended or highly recommended for according to the applied ASIL level, these&#xD;
    include System design inspection, system design walkthroughs, simulation and safety analyses.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If a model based approach is developed further, with the appropriate tools it is possible that system prototyping and&#xD;
    vehicle tests can also be carried out.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The use of a model based approach at this level is especially useful for helping develop the item and integration test&#xD;
    plans.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This could be considered to be a variant on the architectural analysis phase of system development detailed&amp;nbsp;in &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/Architectural%20Design%20-%20uc_E8CAF5DD.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_H1zdAa3hEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>Architectural Design - Use-Case based&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;or &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../process.syseng.base-ibm/deliveryprocesses/Architectural%20Design%20-%20op_54664526.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_E9oWAa3hEd63sNXoX4A_sA&quot;>Architectural Design - Operation based&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;depending upon the approach being&#xD;
    taken.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-WbrG9sM9oq20cTudp4SBcg" name="Verify system and HW SW design,_d7GcQJzkEeCk2aQcgmZB_w" guid="-WbrG9sM9oq20cTudp4SBcg">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    In this task the following methods and measures should be considered.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;table dir=&quot;ltr&quot; border=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;2&quot; width=&quot;631&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot; valign=&quot;center&quot; rowspan=&quot;2&quot; width=&quot;70%&quot; colspan=&quot;2&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>Methods&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;30%&quot; colspan=&quot;4&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>ASIL&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;8%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>A&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;6%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;b>B&lt;/b>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot; valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;7%&quot;>&#xD;
