  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-aE4qEab-qpkoRGYr1ThbjQ" name="Develop HW and SW inteface specification,_-wn-UZwUEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-aE4qEab-qpkoRGYr1ThbjQ">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The specifications covers all points of interaction of components involved in a technical safety concept.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Details can be found in ISO 26262 Vol 4, Clause 7.4.6&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For an example of content of an HSI report it is recommended that the user refers to ISO 26262, vol 4, Annex B.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If using a model based approach it&amp;nbsp;is also possible to derive the HSI specification directly from the model using&#xD;
    an appropriate document template with the modeling tool.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-JiXlUNvr7pKYgxoffIjliQ" name="Develop requirements for production, operation service and decommissioning,_-wn-UpwUEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-JiXlUNvr7pKYgxoffIjliQ">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Means to support the capturing of data from field shall be established. The extent of this data is based upon the&#xD;
    results of the safety analysis and implemented safety mechanisms.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Diagnostic features should be implemented in the system design to allow service staff to identify faults.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Requirements that need to be considered for this task include, assembly instructions, proper identification of&#xD;
    components, safety related special characteristics, verification measures for production,servicing/fault diagnostics,&#xD;
    decomissioning etc.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-R0ZO4dJ-7T4b-gtmB9fmdQ" name="Develop system design specification,_-wn-U5wUEeCHd41ThlqoSg" guid="-R0ZO4dJ-7T4b-gtmB9fmdQ">
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The System design specification defines the architecture and functionality&amp;nbsp;of the system.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If using model based techniques the systems design specification can be derived from the model using the appropriate&#xD;
    document template for the tools being used.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
